<h3 data-mw-thread-id="h-Are_you_opposing_the_shift_to_CC-BY-SA_3.0?_It_seems_a_really_great_idea.-Preliminary_questions_and_answers-2009-07-21T20:01:00.000Z"><span id="Are_you_opposing_the_shift_to_CC-BY-SA_3.0.3F_It_seems_a_really_great_idea."></span><span class="mw-headline" id="Are_you_opposing_the_shift_to_CC-BY-SA_3.0?_It_seems_a_really_great_idea."><span data-mw-comment-start="" id="h-Are_you_opposing_the_shift_to_CC-BY-SA_3.0?_It_seems_a_really_great_idea.-Preliminary_questions_and_answers-2009-07-21T20:01:00.000Z"></span>Are you opposing the shift to CC-BY-SA 3.0? It seems a really great idea.<span data-mw-comment-end="h-Are_you_opposing_the_shift_to_CC-BY-SA_3.0?_It_seems_a_really_great_idea.-Preliminary_questions_and_answers-2009-07-21T20:01:00.000Z"></span></span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Licensing_update/Questions_and_Answers/Oppositional_arguments&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2" title="Edit section: Are you opposing the shift to CC-BY-SA 3.0? It seems a really great idea."><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<p><span data-mw-comment-start="" id="c-Canp-2009-07-21T20:01:00.000Z-Are_you_opposing_the_shift_to_CC-BY-SA_3.0?_It_seems_a_really_great_idea."></span>It is a great idea. Erik Moller’s “terms of service” however are not.
</p>
<dl><dd><dl><dd>@Erik: Why??? Why are you punishing us with your @%#$&amp;! incomprehensible Terms of Service.... :O :P ;) <a href="/w/index.php?title=User:Canp&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="User:Canp (page does not exist)">Canp</a> <a href="https://meta.wikimedia.org/wiki/Licensing_update/Questions_and_Answers/Oppositional_arguments#c-Canp-2009-07-21T20:01:00.000Z-Are_you_opposing_the_shift_to_CC-BY-SA_3.0?_It_seems_a_really_great_idea." class="ext-discussiontools-init-timestamplink">20:01, 21 July 2009 (UTC)</a><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-buttons" data-mw-thread-id="c-Canp-2009-07-21T20:01:00.000Z-Are_you_opposing_the_shift_to_CC-BY-SA_3.0?_It_seems_a_really_great_idea."><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">[</span><a class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-reply" role="button" tabindex="0" href="">reply</a><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">]</span><!--__DTELLIPSISBUTTON__{"threadItem":{"timestamp":"2009-07-21T20:01:00.000Z","author":"Canp","type":"comment","level":1,"id":"c-Canp-2009-07-21T20:01:00.000Z-Are_you_opposing_the_shift_to_CC-BY-SA_3.0?_It_seems_a_really_great_idea.","replies":[]}}--></span><span data-mw-comment-end="c-Canp-2009-07-21T20:01:00.000Z-Are_you_opposing_the_shift_to_CC-BY-SA_3.0?_It_seems_a_really_great_idea."></span></dd>
<dd>P.S.: Ofcourse this was just a joke.</dd></dl></dd></dl>
<h3 data-mw-thread-id="h-So_what’s_the_problem_with_the_TOS?_(Terms_of_Service)-Preliminary_questions_and_answers-2009-05-05T20:54:00.000Z"><span id="So_what.E2.80.99s_the_problem_with_the_TOS.3F_.28Terms_of_Service.29"></span><span class="mw-headline" id="So_what’s_the_problem_with_the_TOS?_(Terms_of_Service)"><span data-mw-comment-start="" id="h-So_what’s_the_problem_with_the_TOS?_(Terms_of_Service)-Preliminary_questions_and_answers-2009-05-05T20:54:00.000Z"></span>So what’s the problem with the TOS? (Terms of Service)<span data-mw-comment-end="h-So_what’s_the_problem_with_the_TOS?_(Terms_of_Service)-Preliminary_questions_and_answers-2009-05-05T20:54:00.000Z"></span></span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Licensing_update/Questions_and_Answers/Oppositional_arguments&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3" title="Edit section: So what’s the problem with the TOS? (Terms of Service)"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<p><span data-mw-comment-start="" id="c-Kaldari-2009-05-05T20:54:00.000Z-So_what’s_the_problem_with_the_TOS?_(Terms_of_Service)"></span>In short, it’s not actually legal.
</p><p>The problem comes with Erik’s copyright policy:
</p>
<style data-mw-deduplicate="TemplateStyles:r19611955">.mw-parser-output .templatequote{background-color:#eaf8f4;border-left:3px solid #008560;overflow:hidden;margin:1em 0;padding:0 20px}.mw-parser-output .templatequote .templatequotecite{line-height:1.5em;text-align:left;padding-left:1.6em;margin-top:0}</style><blockquote class="templatequote"><p>To re-distribute an article page, in any form, provide credit to the authors either by including a) a hyperlink (where possible) or URL to the article or articles you are re-using, b) a hyperlink (where possible) or URL to an alternative, stable online copy which is freely accessible, which conforms with the license, and which provides credit to the authors in a manner equivalent to the credit given on this website, or c) a list of all authors. (Any list of authors may be filtered to exclude very small or irrelevant contributions.)
</p></blockquote>
<p>Now let's compare that to what CC-BY-SA-3.0 has to say about attribution:
</p>
<link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r19611955"><blockquote class="templatequote"><p>If You Distribute, or Publicly Perform the Work or any Adaptations or Collections, You must, unless a request has been made pursuant to Section 4(a), keep intact all copyright notices for the Work and provide, reasonable to the medium or means You are utilizing: (i) the name of the Original Author (or pseudonym, if applicable) if supplied, and/or if the Original Author and/or Licensor designate another party or parties (e.g., a sponsor institute, publishing entity, journal) for attribution ("Attribution Parties") in Licensor's copyright notice, terms of service or by other reasonable means, the name of such party or parties; (ii) the title of the Work if supplied; (iii) to the extent reasonably practicable, the URI, if any, that Licensor specifies to be associated with the Work, unless such URI does not refer to the copyright notice or licensing information for the Work;
</p></blockquote>
<p>Attribution must be “reasonable to the medium or means” which will vary from case to case and cannot be flatly declared to always consist of a URL.
</p>
<dl><dd>Why not? I've yet to see a convincing case in which a URL is not a reasonable attribution method. <a href="/wiki/User:Kaldari" title="User:Kaldari">Kaldari</a> <a href="https://meta.wikimedia.org/wiki/Licensing_update/Questions_and_Answers/Oppositional_arguments#c-Kaldari-2009-05-05T20:54:00.000Z-So_what’s_the_problem_with_the_TOS?_(Terms_of_Service)" class="ext-discussiontools-init-timestamplink">20:54, 5 May 2009 (UTC)</a><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-buttons" data-mw-thread-id="c-Kaldari-2009-05-05T20:54:00.000Z-So_what’s_the_problem_with_the_TOS?_(Terms_of_Service)"><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">[</span><a class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-reply" role="button" tabindex="0" href="">reply</a><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">]</span><!--__DTELLIPSISBUTTON__{"threadItem":{"timestamp":"2009-05-05T20:54:00.000Z","author":"Kaldari","type":"comment","level":1,"id":"c-Kaldari-2009-05-05T20:54:00.000Z-So_what\u2019s_the_problem_with_the_TOS?_(Terms_of_Service)","replies":[]}}--></span><span data-mw-comment-end="c-Kaldari-2009-05-05T20:54:00.000Z-So_what’s_the_problem_with_the_TOS?_(Terms_of_Service)"></span></dd></dl>
<h3 data-mw-thread-id="h-Doesn’t_the_Attribution_Parties_clause_allow_for_this?-Preliminary_questions_and_answers"><span id="Doesn.E2.80.99t_the_Attribution_Parties_clause_allow_for_this.3F"></span><span class="mw-headline" id="Doesn’t_the_Attribution_Parties_clause_allow_for_this?"><span data-mw-comment-start="" id="h-Doesn’t_the_Attribution_Parties_clause_allow_for_this?-Preliminary_questions_and_answers"></span>Doesn’t the Attribution Parties clause allow for this?<span data-mw-comment-end="h-Doesn’t_the_Attribution_Parties_clause_allow_for_this?-Preliminary_questions_and_answers"></span></span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Licensing_update/Questions_and_Answers/Oppositional_arguments&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4" title="Edit section: Doesn’t the Attribution Parties clause allow for this?"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<p>No, since that can only be used for new edits since the GFDL 1.3 doesn’t create any Attribution Parties in the shift to CC-BY-SA-3.0. As a result, the English Wikipedia alone has over 290 million edits that the Attribution Parties clause can’t be used for.
</p>
<h3 data-mw-thread-id="h-What_about_clause_(iii)_the_URI,_if_any,_that_Licensor_specifies_to_be_associate-Preliminary_questions_and_answers"><span id="What_about_clause_.28iii.29_the_URI.2C_if_any.2C_that_Licensor_specifies_to_be_associated_with_the_Work.3F"></span><span class="mw-headline" id="What_about_clause_(iii)_the_URI,_if_any,_that_Licensor_specifies_to_be_associated_with_the_Work?"><span data-mw-comment-start="" id="h-What_about_clause_(iii)_the_URI,_if_any,_that_Licensor_specifies_to_be_associate-Preliminary_questions_and_answers"></span>What about clause (iii) the URI, if any, that Licensor specifies to be associated with the Work?<span data-mw-comment-end="h-What_about_clause_(iii)_the_URI,_if_any,_that_Licensor_specifies_to_be_associate-Preliminary_questions_and_answers"></span></span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Licensing_update/Questions_and_Answers/Oppositional_arguments&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5" title="Edit section: What about clause (iii) the URI, if any, that Licensor specifies to be associated with the Work?"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<p>The problem with that approach is that as the license is phrased that is in addition to the requirement to provide attribution reasonable to the medium or means.
</p>
<h3 data-mw-thread-id="h-But_isn’t_including_a_full_list_of_authors_unreasonable_in_so_many_cases?-Preliminary_questions_and_answers-2009-04-22T02:48:00.000Z"><span id="But_isn.E2.80.99t_including_a_full_list_of_authors_unreasonable_in_so_many_cases.3F"></span><span class="mw-headline" id="But_isn’t_including_a_full_list_of_authors_unreasonable_in_so_many_cases?"><span data-mw-comment-start="" id="h-But_isn’t_including_a_full_list_of_authors_unreasonable_in_so_many_cases?-Preliminary_questions_and_answers-2009-04-22T02:48:00.000Z"></span>But isn’t including a full list of authors unreasonable in so many cases?<span data-mw-comment-end="h-But_isn’t_including_a_full_list_of_authors_unreasonable_in_so_many_cases?-Preliminary_questions_and_answers-2009-04-22T02:48:00.000Z"></span></span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Licensing_update/Questions_and_Answers/Oppositional_arguments&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6" title="Edit section: But isn’t including a full list of authors unreasonable in so many cases?"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<p><span data-mw-comment-start="" id="c-Jesdisciple-2009-04-22T02:48:00.000Z-But_isn’t_including_a_full_list_of_authors_unreasonable_in_so_many_cases?"></span>There are also cases where attribution by URL would be highly problematical. CC-BY-SA 3.0 allows for that by allowing attribution to be reasonable to the medium and means. This however is something that has to be worked out on a case by case basis and not something the Foundation can declare by fiat.
</p>
<dl><dd>I'm curious about what case(s) would render both the list and the URL problematic. --<a href="/wiki/User:Jesdisciple" title="User:Jesdisciple">Jesdisciple</a> <a href="https://meta.wikimedia.org/wiki/Licensing_update/Questions_and_Answers/Oppositional_arguments#c-Jesdisciple-2009-04-22T02:48:00.000Z-But_isn’t_including_a_full_list_of_authors_unreasonable_in_so_many_cases?" class="ext-discussiontools-init-timestamplink">02:48, 22 April 2009 (UTC)</a><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-buttons" data-mw-thread-id="c-Jesdisciple-2009-04-22T02:48:00.000Z-But_isn’t_including_a_full_list_of_authors_unreasonable_in_so_many_cases?"><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">[</span><a class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-reply" role="button" tabindex="0" href="">reply</a><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">]</span><!--__DTELLIPSISBUTTON__{"threadItem":{"timestamp":"2009-04-22T02:48:00.000Z","author":"Jesdisciple","type":"comment","level":1,"id":"c-Jesdisciple-2009-04-22T02:48:00.000Z-But_isn\u2019t_including_a_full_list_of_authors_unreasonable_in_so_many_cases?","replies":["c-Genisock2-2009-04-29T21:46:00.000Z-Jesdisciple-2009-04-22T02:48:00.000Z"]}}--></span><span data-mw-comment-end="c-Jesdisciple-2009-04-22T02:48:00.000Z-But_isn’t_including_a_full_list_of_authors_unreasonable_in_so_many_cases?"></span>
<dl><dd><span data-mw-comment-start="" id="c-Genisock2-2009-04-29T21:46:00.000Z-Jesdisciple-2009-04-22T02:48:00.000Z"></span>3D media can present issue. You also hit a bunch of problems with what is meant by a URL in this case being poorly defined with the result that if you embed enough info in QR Code to trigger crediting requirements what counts as a ULR in this case?<a href="/w/index.php?title=User:Genisock2&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="User:Genisock2 (page does not exist)">Genisock2</a> <a href="https://meta.wikimedia.org/wiki/Licensing_update/Questions_and_Answers/Oppositional_arguments#c-Genisock2-2009-04-29T21:46:00.000Z-Jesdisciple-2009-04-22T02:48:00.000Z" class="ext-discussiontools-init-timestamplink">21:46, 29 April 2009 (UTC)</a><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-buttons" data-mw-thread-id="c-Genisock2-2009-04-29T21:46:00.000Z-Jesdisciple-2009-04-22T02:48:00.000Z"><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">[</span><a class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-reply" role="button" tabindex="0" href="">reply</a><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">]</span><!--__DTELLIPSISBUTTON__{"threadItem":{"timestamp":"2009-04-29T21:46:00.000Z","author":"Genisock2","type":"comment","level":3,"id":"c-Genisock2-2009-04-29T21:46:00.000Z-Jesdisciple-2009-04-22T02:48:00.000Z","replies":["c-Kaldari-2009-05-05T20:52:00.000Z-Genisock2-2009-04-29T21:46:00.000Z"]}}--></span><span data-mw-comment-end="c-Genisock2-2009-04-29T21:46:00.000Z-Jesdisciple-2009-04-22T02:48:00.000Z"></span>
<dl><dd><span data-mw-comment-start="" id="c-Kaldari-2009-05-05T20:52:00.000Z-Genisock2-2009-04-29T21:46:00.000Z"></span>Why are URLs a problem in 3D media? I can't parse your 2nd sentence at all. <a href="/wiki/User:Kaldari" title="User:Kaldari">Kaldari</a> <a href="https://meta.wikimedia.org/wiki/Licensing_update/Questions_and_Answers/Oppositional_arguments#c-Kaldari-2009-05-05T20:52:00.000Z-Genisock2-2009-04-29T21:46:00.000Z" class="ext-discussiontools-init-timestamplink">20:52, 5 May 2009 (UTC)</a><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-buttons" data-mw-thread-id="c-Kaldari-2009-05-05T20:52:00.000Z-Genisock2-2009-04-29T21:46:00.000Z"><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">[</span><a class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-reply" role="button" tabindex="0" href="">reply</a><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">]</span><!--__DTELLIPSISBUTTON__{"threadItem":{"timestamp":"2009-05-05T20:52:00.000Z","author":"Kaldari","type":"comment","level":4,"id":"c-Kaldari-2009-05-05T20:52:00.000Z-Genisock2-2009-04-29T21:46:00.000Z","replies":[]}}--></span><span data-mw-comment-end="c-Kaldari-2009-05-05T20:52:00.000Z-Genisock2-2009-04-29T21:46:00.000Z"></span></dd></dl></dd></dl></dd></dl>
<h3 data-mw-thread-id="h-But_we_can_fudge_it,_right?-Preliminary_questions_and_answers"><span id="But_we_can_fudge_it.2C_right.3F"></span><span class="mw-headline" id="But_we_can_fudge_it,_right?"><span data-mw-comment-start="" id="h-But_we_can_fudge_it,_right?-Preliminary_questions_and_answers"></span>But we can fudge it, right?<span data-mw-comment-end="h-But_we_can_fudge_it,_right?-Preliminary_questions_and_answers"></span></span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Licensing_update/Questions_and_Answers/Oppositional_arguments&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7" title="Edit section: But we can fudge it, right?"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<p>No. Firstly, it’s clearly not legal. But even if it was less clear, the switch away from GFDL is meant to clear up some of the legal uncertainties associated with the GFDL. Creating new ones would appear to be counter productive. In addition, if there was a way to fudge it the resulting fudge would prevent third party CC-BY-SA-3.0 being brought into Wikipedia, because the author would very clearly not have agreed to Wikipedia’s terms of service.
</p>
<h3 data-mw-thread-id="h-But_hasn’t_the_board_endorsed_this?-Preliminary_questions_and_answers"><span id="But_hasn.E2.80.99t_the_board_endorsed_this.3F"></span><span class="mw-headline" id="But_hasn’t_the_board_endorsed_this?"><span data-mw-comment-start="" id="h-But_hasn’t_the_board_endorsed_this?-Preliminary_questions_and_answers"></span>But hasn’t the board endorsed this?<span data-mw-comment-end="h-But_hasn’t_the_board_endorsed_this?-Preliminary_questions_and_answers"></span></span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Licensing_update/Questions_and_Answers/Oppositional_arguments&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8" title="Edit section: But hasn’t the board endorsed this?"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<p>The board statement endorses the switch to CC-BY-SA-3.0. It makes no mention of terms of service or copyright notices whatsoever.
</p>
<h3 data-mw-thread-id="h-Hasn&#039;t_the_TOS_been_validated_by_Creative_Commons_General_Counsel?-Preliminary_questions_and_answers-2009-04-14T20:49:00.000Z"><span id="Hasn.27t_the_TOS_been_validated_by_Creative_Commons_General_Counsel.3F"></span><span class="mw-headline" id="Hasn't_the_TOS_been_validated_by_Creative_Commons_General_Counsel?"><span data-mw-comment-start="" id="h-Hasn't_the_TOS_been_validated_by_Creative_Commons_General_Counsel?-Preliminary_questions_and_answers-2009-04-14T20:49:00.000Z"></span>Hasn't the TOS been validated by Creative Commons General Counsel?<span data-mw-comment-end="h-Hasn't_the_TOS_been_validated_by_Creative_Commons_General_Counsel?-Preliminary_questions_and_answers-2009-04-14T20:49:00.000Z"></span></span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Licensing_update/Questions_and_Answers/Oppositional_arguments&amp;action=edit&amp;section=9" title="Edit section: Hasn&#039;t the TOS been validated by Creative Commons General Counsel?"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<p><span data-mw-comment-start="" id="c-Calandrella-2009-04-14T20:49:00.000Z-Hasn't_the_TOS_been_validated_by_Creative_Commons_General_Counsel?"></span>People claimed that they have, but that doesn't help since we have no idea what question was asked. It's fairly trivial to ask a question that would give you the answer that the TOS were legit, but not in a way that applies to the situation on Wikipedia. There is also the issue that CC have a massive conflict of interest.
</p>
<dl><dd>"It's fairly trivial to ask a question that would give you the answer that the TOS were legit but not in a way that applies to the situation on wikipedia" Why do you think so? And why wouldn't the question be asked in a good way? <a href="/wiki/User:Calandrella" title="User:Calandrella">Calandrella</a> <a href="https://meta.wikimedia.org/wiki/Licensing_update/Questions_and_Answers/Oppositional_arguments#c-Calandrella-2009-04-14T20:49:00.000Z-Hasn't_the_TOS_been_validated_by_Creative_Commons_General_Counsel?" class="ext-discussiontools-init-timestamplink">20:49, 14 April 2009 (UTC)</a><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-buttons" data-mw-thread-id="c-Calandrella-2009-04-14T20:49:00.000Z-Hasn't_the_TOS_been_validated_by_Creative_Commons_General_Counsel?"><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">[</span><a class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-reply" role="button" tabindex="0" href="">reply</a><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">]</span><!--__DTELLIPSISBUTTON__{"threadItem":{"timestamp":"2009-04-14T20:49:00.000Z","author":"Calandrella","type":"comment","level":1,"id":"c-Calandrella-2009-04-14T20:49:00.000Z-Hasn't_the_TOS_been_validated_by_Creative_Commons_General_Counsel?","replies":["c-Geni-2009-04-14T22:35:00.000Z-Calandrella-2009-04-14T20:49:00.000Z"]}}--></span><span data-mw-comment-end="c-Calandrella-2009-04-14T20:49:00.000Z-Hasn't_the_TOS_been_validated_by_Creative_Commons_General_Counsel?"></span></dd></dl>
<dl><dd><dl><dd><span data-mw-comment-start="" id="c-Geni-2009-04-14T22:35:00.000Z-Calandrella-2009-04-14T20:49:00.000Z"></span>The question "are these TOS allowable under CC-BY-SA-3.0?" would appear to be relevant but isn't (the answer BTW is mostly yes). A more relevant question would be "Can these TOS be imposed on content ported over from GFDL 1.4?" (to which the answer is no) but I have no evidence that that type of question has actually been asked. Requests for precise wordings of questions come to nothing and I wouldn't expect people to ask the second form.<a href="/wiki/User:Geni" title="User:Geni">Geni</a> <a href="https://meta.wikimedia.org/wiki/Licensing_update/Questions_and_Answers/Oppositional_arguments#c-Geni-2009-04-14T22:35:00.000Z-Calandrella-2009-04-14T20:49:00.000Z" class="ext-discussiontools-init-timestamplink">22:35, 14 April 2009 (UTC)</a><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-buttons" data-mw-thread-id="c-Geni-2009-04-14T22:35:00.000Z-Calandrella-2009-04-14T20:49:00.000Z"><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">[</span><a class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-reply" role="button" tabindex="0" href="">reply</a><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">]</span><!--__DTELLIPSISBUTTON__{"threadItem":{"timestamp":"2009-04-14T22:35:00.000Z","author":"Geni","type":"comment","level":3,"id":"c-Geni-2009-04-14T22:35:00.000Z-Calandrella-2009-04-14T20:49:00.000Z","replies":[]}}--></span><span data-mw-comment-end="c-Geni-2009-04-14T22:35:00.000Z-Calandrella-2009-04-14T20:49:00.000Z"></span></dd></dl></dd></dl>
